para_trans: Government Decision No: BCC 1125 / P.No.70 (e-Nasti No. 1276776) / Reservation-5
The scope of the said Cabinet Sub-Committee shall be as follows: -
1. To co-ordinate the administrative and legislative work on Maratha reservation.
2. Appointed to represent the Government in judicial cases in this regard.
Coordinating with counselors, giving suggestions to special counselors.
3. To lay down the procedure for implementation of the order passed by the Court of Appeal.
4. Coordination with the Justice Sandeep Shinde Committee. difficulties in their work.
to resolve.
5. Discussion with Maratha protesters and their delegation.
6. Deciding on the difficulties in issuing caste certificates and streamlining the process.
to take action.
7. Schemes announced for the Maratha community as well as Sarathi and Annasaheb Patil finances.
Schemes implemented for the Maratha community through the Development Corporation.
Review and control of implementation.
3. The said proposed Cabinet Sub-Committee shall be assisted by experts for exchange of views as required.
Jurists, and the relevant authorities, etc. will have the power to invite.
4. This Government Decision is available on the Government of Maharashtra website www.maharashtra.gov.in.
